we speak bow wow equipped with a keen intuition , great confidence , and credentials stacked sky high , kate solisti - mattelon steps up and ably swats one home for the dog lover in us all . she has long understood that dogs run the wide and crooked . it 's we humans who took the broad view and tried to fit it into the straight and narrow scope of understanding . an awkward fit at best , if not totally improbable . she presents her material simply , in a parable format of sorts to help us understand the heart and mind of man 's best friend . repeated readings pay off . myself , having to resolve grief issues on having to put my thirteen years old siberian husky , riva to sleep this past summer . i now know without doubt that my favorite life companion is a part of me forever . this book can and should be a part of you . highly enjoyable . highly recommended